The paper deals with the problem of image cropping for visual aesthetic enhancement, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses deep neural networks (cs.AI) and cascaded regression (cs.LG) to perform the image cropping. The paper also mentions the use of large-scale visual aesthetic datasets (cs.MM) and the problem of lacking labelled cropping data, which can be addressed using information retrieval techniques (cs.IR).
